==English==
===Etymology===
See the Wikipedia article [[w:ISO 216|ISO 216]], the international standard on paper sizes.

===Noun===
'''A0'''
# The base size in the series of the [[international standard]]. Set such that it has an area of 1 [[square metre]], where the [[ratio]] between the width and the length equals [[square root]] of 2. The width of each size is equal to the length of next smaller size.
#: dimensions: 1189 x 841 mm  (1189.21 x 840.90 mm)

